race.comment: Absolute lottery with huge pressure up front. BEEN A SECRET (1) was a fresh-up winner then runner-up at Gatton last time. Looks suited by the extra trip now and is a third-up winner. Give another chance. BUTT HEADS (6) raced on speed before fading here in river grade. Previous form strong and looks well placed. Goes well here at home and worth another chance. ZHENG YOU (5)  is an honest galloper who is second up today after finishing sixth over 1200m at Doomben when resuming five-and-a-half weeks ago. Will strip fitter this time and drawn for a soft run with cover. Gets chance to find winning form.  I'M LUCKY TWO (12) hasn't been beaten all that far in recent outings, the latest a third over 1100m at this track two weeks ago. First try this trip and will be pushing forward.
